Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.00,0:00:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and get out.\NThe police will be here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.01,0:00:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.84,0:00:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to Dresden.\NWait in the train station square.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.81,0:00:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.11,0:00:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.82,0:00:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,"Cedok Bridge.The Three Frogs"?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.20,0:00:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,My father also told me this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.07,0:00:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,"If the monster\Nyou are chasing has a twin…"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.99,0:00:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The twins' mother is alive\Nand living in Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.55,0:02:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.47,0:02:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.64,0:02:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.81,0:02:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,-Stop it!\N-Pass it here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.06,0:02:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over there now!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.31,0:02:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Cut it out! Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.82,0:02:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Any luck, Mr. Grimmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.82,0:02:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you find the documents\Nyou were looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.45,0:02:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Since East and West Germany reunified,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.37,0:02:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,this school has completely changed\Nhow it operates.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.20,0:02:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are all the documents\Nthat remain from before.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.33,0:02:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to put you in all this trouble,\NDirector Galbreckt.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.25,0:02:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's actually pretty rare\Nto find this much remaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.84,0:02:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the fall of the Berlin Wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.43,0:02:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,nearly all records of East Germany's\Nunethical practices disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.43,0:03:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's quite clear\Nthat there was child abuse
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.35,0:03:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,at the orphanages in former East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.98,0:03:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's hard to find documents\Nthat prove that kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.24,0:03:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.07,0:03:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Orphanages in East Germany were
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.32,0:03:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,administered by\Nthe Ministry of Health and Welfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.25,0:03:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The biggest issue is with children\Nof parents designated as criminals,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.75,0:03:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,anarchists, spies,\Nillegal immigrants, or failed defectors.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.71,0:03:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the institutions\Nthat took care of these children
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.09,0:03:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,was Kinderheim, which was run by the\Nnotorious Ministry of Internal Affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.93,0:03:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unclear just how much abuse\Nand inhumane brainwashing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.35,0:03:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,took place in this one special orphanage.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.98,0:03:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what I am trying to find out\Nin as much detail as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.40,0:03:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know what happened there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.36,0:03:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave no stone unturned.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.57,0:03:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No stone unturned, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.49,0:04:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. That sounds like quite a task.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.58,0:04:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone who worked there must either\Nbe in exile or isn't talking, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.46,0:04:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.29,0:04:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Mr. Schnurr, an instructor here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.54,0:04:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Schnurr?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.67,0:04:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a teacher at 62 Kinderheim\Nin former East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.05,0:04:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked to speak with him,\Nbut he turned me down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.60,0:04:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You should keep an eye on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.22,0:04:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a possibility\Nthat Mr. Schnurr abused children
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.27,0:04:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,when he worked in East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.90,0:04:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Would it be all right\Nif I made copies of these documents?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.82,0:04:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.57,0:04:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.66,0:04:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you're a journalist from\Nthe former West Germany, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.58,0:04:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I was a journalist for a newspaper\Nin Leipzig here in the east.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.92,0:04:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? I'm surprised that a human rights\Nactivist like you was in the east.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.84,0:04:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, well…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.43,0:05:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, I went all around\Nthe world as a foreign correspondent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.06,0:05:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They were all missions for the government.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.44,0:05:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,-Understand what I mean?\N-Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.44,0:05:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.53,0:05:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.99,0:05:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's quite a bag you have there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.95,0:05:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's packed with documents I've picked up\Nfrom all over former East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.54,0:05:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to read\Nwhat you put together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.75,0:05:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So where are you headed next?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.13,0:05:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Prague in the Czech Republic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.96,0:05:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate your cooperation,\NDirector Galbreckt.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.73,0:05:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Those other kids\Nsure were pretty mean to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.74,0:06:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess they ended up\Ntaking your shoes, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.11,0:06:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now. Stop crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.50,0:06:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We humans can do just fine without shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.43,0:06:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We were born barefoot, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.26,0:06:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But I must say,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.02,0:06:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,anyone who would bully others\Nand take their shoes is scum.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.98,0:06:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason to let scum\Nlike them make you cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.77,0:06:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.96,0:07:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess they're too big\Nto even walk in, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.26,0:07:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,DRESDEN STATION
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.89,0:07:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,-Sir, excuse me.\N-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.73,0:07:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,May I bother you for a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.07,0:07:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.78,0:07:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, actually,\NI've run into a little problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.32,0:07:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The bag with my passport in it was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.20,0:07:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Your passport? Oh dear, that's awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.08,0:07:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.08,0:07:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I was on my way\Nto see my sister in Vienna.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.34,0:07:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,My other sister called yesterday\Nto tell me she had collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.38,0:07:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She did? Then you'd better go and see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.59,0:07:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You should report it to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.64,0:07:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay. I already have.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.47,0:07:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is my sister doesn't have\Nthe money to pay the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.31,0:07:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.44,0:08:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,My wallet was also in the bag\Nthat was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.69,0:08:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't go now,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.20,0:08:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but if I could at least send some money,\Nit would help my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.74,0:08:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't even do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.28,0:08:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How much do you need?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.33,0:08:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you don't need to do that.\NI don't need that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.67,0:08:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All I need is enough to pay for her to be\Ntaken to the hospital and see a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.26,0:08:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all I can manage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.43,0:08:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.80,0:08:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I swear I'll pay you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.35,0:08:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Write down your address on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.43,0:08:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.27,0:08:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just glad if can help\Nyour sister get care.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.27,0:08:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. You're a lifesaver!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.77,0:08:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope she gets well soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.03,0:08:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, what did you give him money for?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.57,0:08:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.49,0:08:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That guy's clearly lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.70,0:08:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.12,0:08:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,People like him are always hanging out\Nat the station looking for easy targets.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.25,0:09:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you let yourself get duped?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.92,0:09:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I got duped?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.88,0:09:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The express to Prague leaves\Nplatform seven at 3:15 p.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.18,0:09:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.57,0:09:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,-Thanks, I appreciate it.\N-Don't mention it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.21,0:09:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.93,0:09:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,May I sit here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.55,0:09:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.69,0:10:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you headed?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.31,0:10:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,To Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.42,0:10:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,-You're Japanese, aren't you?\N-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.59,0:10:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Konnichiwa.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.09,0:10:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Domo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.17,0:10:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been to Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.59,0:10:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.09,0:10:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,How many years ago was that?\NI remember now, it was 1982.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.68,0:10:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I went to Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.81,0:10:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I bought a bunch of listening devices\Nand high-tech equipment there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.65,0:10:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a very popular song then too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.82,0:10:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see. How does it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.40,0:10:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Kita no hakabadori na ha
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.16,0:10:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.33,0:11:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Kita no…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.08,0:11:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Sakabadori ni ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.79,0:11:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. That's how it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.42,0:11:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Kita no sakabadori ni ha
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.67,0:11:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I also bought a plastic model\Nof a robot for my kid. He loved it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.68,0:11:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's your son now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.27,0:11:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he's dead now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.65,0:11:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Immigration control.\NI need to check your passports.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.11,0:11:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.37,0:11:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.05,0:11:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The river Elbe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.47,0:12:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what the trout are like\Nthis year.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.56,0:12:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Not very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.31,0:12:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.27,0:12:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Last year I caught one this big.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.40,0:12:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Not this year, you won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.82,0:12:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.24,0:12:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows your passport is a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.21,0:12:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You better get out of here, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.09,0:12:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know who I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.93,0:12:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind that.\NNow that immigration control realizes
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.68,0:12:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,your passport is a fake,\Nthey'll come after you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.81,0:12:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You better get out of here now, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.74,0:13:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Darn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.71,0:13:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.75,0:13:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to get past.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.67,0:13:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.21,0:13:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,My bag's so big, it's gotten stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.67,0:13:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It just won't budge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.34,0:13:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your darn problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.30,0:13:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't jostle it around too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.26,0:13:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck's inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.51,0:13:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Some very precious items.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.44,0:13:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch! At last, it's free.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.15,0:13:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the man who was here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.95,0:13:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.91,0:13:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember the Asian man\Nwho was here earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.08,0:13:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe he went to the dining car.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.50,0:13:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,-You go check the next car.\N-Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.91,0:13:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This is passenger car two.\NThere's an emergency!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.42,0:13:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,An Asian passenger is carrying\Na fake passport!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.21,0:14:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,-What's wrong?\N-What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.05,0:14:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop the train immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.95,0:14:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done. Very well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.37,0:14:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They haven't come this way\Nlooking for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.04,0:14:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the train stopped, I got off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.05,0:14:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't introduced myself. I'm Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.68,0:14:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,How about I guide you to the border,\NDr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.44,0:15:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I know this area well.\NI often come here to fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.99,0:15:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiking through the mountains\Nwon't be easy,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.70,0:15:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but the views will be worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.04,0:15:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How come you're helping me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.38,0:15:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.92,0:15:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I worked for a newspaper\Nwhen Germany was still split.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.51,0:15:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a freelance journalist now though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.64,0:15:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I've read all the articles about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.06,0:15:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm quite interested in your story.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.60,0:15:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In East Germany, being falsely accused\Nof crimes was a daily occurrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.11,0:15:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Political prisoners were framed\Nwith false murder charges.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.28,0:15:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,After seeing all that,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.82,0:15:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it became pretty easy to tell\Nreal criminals from the falsely accused.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.78,0:15:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You're innocent.\NIsn't that right, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.58,0:15:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Please stop calling me "doctor."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.21,0:16:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What? But you're a talented neurosurgeon,\Naren't you, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.30,0:16:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not a doctor anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.40,0:16:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you like it?\NA darn good view, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.48,0:16:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,From here, we can see\Nif anyone's coming after us too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.82,0:16:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All right then,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.62,0:16:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,why don't we take a little break here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.33,0:16:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,How about a sandwich?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.75,0:16:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought wine as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.21,0:16:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And some delicious cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.25,0:16:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have time for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.63,0:16:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun's still high in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.42,0:16:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You're better off waiting until dark\Nbefore crossing the border.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.52,0:16:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Picnics sure are fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.14,0:17:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This kind of thing is nice\Nevery now and then, isn't it, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.48,0:17:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got magnificent scenery\Nand marvelous food.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.36,0:17:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's times like this\Nwhen we can feel the joy of being alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.33,0:17:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I respect doctors like yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.00,0:17:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,When a journalist like me\Nwrites a good article,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.33,0:17:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I can sometimes help people\Nexperience the joy of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.05,0:17:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can give people\Nthe gift of life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.05,0:17:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I have…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.05,0:17:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I have shot a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.98,0:17:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Last month in Munich,\NI shot a man for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.74,0:17:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He's probably dead too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.04,0:18:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Before that, my hands would tremble\Nand I couldn't aim straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.08,0:18:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But after shooting a man once,\Nmy hands stopped trembling.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.09,0:18:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And now,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.84,0:18:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I am going to have to shoot another man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.48,0:18:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I am… no longer a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.45,0:18:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time I come to the Elbe,\NI think about
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.96,0:18:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,how I would have liked to\Nhave brought my son to fish here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.92,0:18:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean your dead son?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.76,0:18:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You can catch trout this big.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.55,0:19:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He died without even knowing\Nthe joy of fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.06,0:19:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If there had been\Na doctor like yourself nearby then,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.81,0:19:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he could have been saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.78,0:19:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean it.\NYou really can catch trout this big.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.17,0:19:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Cross those mountains\Nand you'll be in the Czech Republic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.88,0:19:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get to the forest road beyond it,\Nyou can probably hitchhike a ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.72,0:19:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go back to the station from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.72,0:19:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYou've been an immense help, Mr. Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.35,0:19:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish you luck,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.98,0:19:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.77,0:19:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's have a picnic again\Nthe next time we meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.91,0:20:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.37,0:20:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is burdened with their sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.25,0:20:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll never go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.04,0:20:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so,\Nwe still carry on with what we must do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.70,0:20:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,PRAGUE (CZECH REPUBLIC)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.04,0:20:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Magnificent.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.62,0:20:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This really is beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.62,0:20:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never been here before,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.17,0:20:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but Prague at night looks like\Na fairytale land.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.56,0:21:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. May I sit here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.35,0:21:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.94,0:21:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I've really fallen in love with this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.32,0:21:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Mr. Petrov, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.36,0:21:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You bought Russian citizenship\Nand now live here in Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.79,0:21:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something I'd like to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.58,0:21:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you be willing to answer\Nsome questions, Mr. Petrov?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.04,0:21:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but isn't your real name\NReinhart Biermann?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.67,0:21:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a special orphanage\Nin East Berlin, wasn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.68,0:21:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The place was like a laboratory\Nfor experimenting
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.72,0:21:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,with chemically induced\Nbrainwashing children.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.43,0:21:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It was called Kinderheim 511.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.89,0:21:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You were the director there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.23,0:22:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Since you were the director,\Nyou must know everything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.11,0:22:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you trying to do there\Nin that place in former East Berlin?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.83,0:22:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There at Kinderheim 511.
